Ghana artiste, Shatta Wale has reacted to the Black Stars’ elimination from the ongoing 2021 Africa Cup of Nations, AFCON, in Cameroon. Ghana was eliminated from the 2021 AFCON in the group stages on Tuesday night following a shock 3-2 defeat to debutants Comoros. The Black Stars came into their final Group C tie with one point and needed a win to progress. Reacting, Wale, in a series of tweets on his verified Twitter handle, said next time he would select the players that will represent Ghana at AFCON. He tweeted, “Ghana has a big problem, it even shows in our football. “Next time I will select the players. “Without a cup what’s the use of milo. “Ghana sef we like hype too much, see how our players deh hype Comoros. Now they are trending.”